      "content": "The rule of law argument deepens when proponents argue that lax enforcement undermines the entire legal framework by creating a system where laws are optional for some. Economically, they contend that unchecked unauthorized immigration can depress wages for low-skilled native workers by increasing labor supply without commensurate skill increases. Philosophically, maintaining a functional society requires clear boundaries and adherence to established legal processes, which enforcement provides to prevent social chaos and resource strain.",
